'''溴化钪'''是一种无机化合物，化学式为ScBr<sub>3</sub>，可溶于水，具有潮解性。

==制备及性质==
溴化钪可由过量的[[氢溴酸|氢溴酸]]和[[氧化钪|氧化钪]]反应製備，从溶液中可以结晶出六水合物。六水合物的热分解只能得到溴氧化钪（ScOBr）和氧化钪。<ref>{{cite journal|journal=Collection of Czechoslovak Chemical Communications|volume=25|issue=4|language=en|issn=0010-0765|date=1960|pages=1143–1147|doi=10.1135/cccc19601143|url=http://cccc.uochb.cas.cz/25/4/1143/|title=Beiträge zur chemie seltener elemente X. Basische scandiumhalogenide|accessdate=2020-07-03|author=F. Petrů, F. Kůtek|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801124516/http://cccc.uochb.cas.cz/25/4/1143/|dead-url=no}}</ref>无水物可由[[溴|溴]]、氧化钪和石墨在氮气中反应制得。<ref>Allen, Robert John; Pullman, Brian J. Chemistry of scandium.  V. ''Amdel Bulletin'', 1968. 5. 52-64. ISSN: 0045-0707.</ref>

[[溴化铵|溴化铵]]和氧化钪或溴化钪的六水合物加热反应，经(NH<sub>4</sub>)<sub>3</sub>ScBr<sub>6</sub>中间体，分解后得到无水溴化钪。<ref>{{cite journal|journal=Journal of the Less Common Metals|volume=127|language=en|date=1987-01|pages=155–160|doi=10.1016/0022-5088(87)90372-9|url=https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/0022508887903729|title=The ammonium-bromide route to anhydrous rare earth bromides MBr3|accessdate=2020-07-03|author=Gerd Meyer, Siegfried Dötsch, Thomas Staffel|archive-date=2020-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200825114804/https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/0022508887903729|dead-url=no}}</ref>

它可以被金属钪还原为低价态的化合物，如ScBr<sub>2.40</sub>等<ref>{{cite journal|journal=Chemical Communications (London)|issue=24|language=en|issn=0009-241X|date=1968|pages=1666|doi=10.1039/c19680001666|url=http://xlink.rsc.org/?DOI=c19680001666|title=The synthesis of reduced scandium chloride, bromide, and iodide phases with unusual stoicheiometries|accessdate=2020-07-03|author=Bill C. McCollum, John D. Corbett}}</ref>；和钪及另一金属（M=Mn, Fe, Ru, Os）在800~900 °C加热，可以得到Sc<sub>19</sub>M<sub>4</sub>Br<sub>28</sub>。<ref>{{cite journal|journal=Inorganic Chemistry|volume=36|issue=27|language=en|issn=0020-1669|date=1997-12|pages=6413–6422|doi=10.1021/ic970881j|url=https://pubs.acs.org/doi/10.1021/ic970881j|title=Syntheses, Crystal Structures, and Magnetic Properties of Sc 19 Br 28 Z 4 Compounds with Z = Mn, Fe, Ru, or Os. Structural and Bonding Trends in R 16 X 20 Z 4 -Type Oligomers|accessdate=2020-07-03|author=Sharon J. Steinwand, John D. Corbett, James D. Martin|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801124519/https://pubs.acs.org/doi/10.1021/ic970881j|dead-url=no}}</ref>

